{
  // Gate CI on HIGH and CRITICAL severity advisories only.
  //
  // WHY NOT all severities: `npm audit` reports advisories against the entire
  // dependency graph regardless of reachability, and this tree's moderate/low
  // advisories are dominated by two unactionable classes:
  //   1. PHANTOM — `dompurify` is pulled by monaco-editor, which VENDORS its own
  //      copy (`esm/vs/base/browser/dompurify/dompurify.js`) and imports THAT,
  //      not the npm package. The npm `dompurify` is never executed; there is no
  //      reachable vulnerability and nothing to fix. The advisory DB mints new
  //      DOMPurify bypass advisories continuously (8 -> 16 in days), so a per-GHSA
  //      allowlist is an unwinnable treadmill.
  //   2. NO CLEAN FIX — transitive advisories whose only remedy is a breaking
  //      upgrade of a parent we don't control (see the accepted list below).
  //
  // Gating on all severities produced constant red CI that blocked unrelated PRs
  // and trains force-merging -- a worse security posture than green CI that fails
  // only on what is actually severe and actionable. High/critical advisories are
  // rare, warrant breaking the build, and are usually fixable. Current tree:
  // 0 high, 0 critical. Run `npm audit` to review the full moderate/low set.
  //
  // KNOWN ACCEPTED moderate/low advisories (informational; below the gate, so not
  // listed as allowlist entries -- re-triage on major dependency upgrades):
  //   - dompurify (via monaco-editor): PHANTOM, see above. No fix possible/needed.
  //   - @opentelemetry/core (via @sentry/node, lighthouse): GHSA-8988-4f7v-96qf,
  //     no fix without a breaking parent bump. REVISIT on the next @sentry/nextjs upgrade.
  //   - postcss (via next): GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93, no fix. REVISIT on the next Next.js upgrade.
  //   - js-yaml (via gray-matter): GHSA-h67p-54hq-rp68; parses ONLY our own
  //     build-time markdown front-matter, never runtime/untrusted input, so the
  //     DoS vector is unreachable. REVISIT on a gray-matter@2 migration.
  //   - @ai-sdk/provider-utils (via ai): GHSA-866g-f22w-33x8 (low). REVISIT on the ai@6 migration.
  //
  // If a HIGH/critical advisory ever lands that is itself phantom/unfixable,
  // allowlist that ONE advisory here by GHSA id with a dated reason -- a rare,
  // deliberate exception, not a standing treadmill.
  "high": true,
  "allowlist": []
}
